The order of the script is as follows: Opening - First word - First word explanation - Second word - Second word explanation - Third word - Third word explanation - Break time - Fourth word - Fourth word explanation - Fifth word - Fifth word explanation - Sixth word - Sixth word explanation - Closing remarks.

In the opening, include an explanation of what neologisms are. 

Choose words that fit the topic (neologisms) and present the meaning of each word in a quiz format. 

To give time for answering, insert about 20 seconds of waiting music. 

Briefly explain the meaning of the word and include comments about the word.

When closing, acknowledge that it might have been difficult because the newly coined words can be awkward, and include encouraging and appreciative remarks.
